lead_paragraph: Jamil Walker scored twice in the second half last night to lead D.C. United to a 3-1 victory over the Red Bulls in Washington in the quarterfinals of the Lamar Hunt U.S. Open Cup. Walker, who has only one goal this season in M.L.S. play, scored in the 61st and 84th minutes, breaking a 1-1 halftime tie. Joshua Gros opened the scoring for United in the 37th minute. The Red Bulls’ Amado Guevara scored in the 41st minute.
